narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A truly fun course. Work may compound if this is your first exposure to the language, but the work all has an educational purpose.
I would recommend Hebrew to someone looking to start a new language because it is a fun language to learn and Ayala is a great teacher.
Great course, definitely take it if you're looking to really learn Hebrew.

Hebrew 110 gives you a lot of work, and a lot of love for Ayala and Hebrew. Its sort of a paradox - it was definitely more work than the rest of my classes combined, but I grew to love Ayala and class so much that it didn't matter. Which is ideal. You end up learning a TON, and wishing Ayala was your Jewish grandmother. Also, definitely there is a variance of knowledge going into class, but it is not a great issue.
Yes take it. You will lezrn a great deal and the class is a pleasure each day.
